<![CDATA[<font face="arial"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Hi&nbsp;{!Contact.FirstName},</span></font><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;"><br></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;">I would like to invite you to be part of the Regional Youth Board. The opportunity to be involved is only for NCS Leaders and one selected person from each 'local' youth board.</div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;"><br></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;">A quick summary of what it involves:</div><div><ul><li><font face="arial">Attending 3/4 meetings in 2016</font></li><li><font face="arial">Meetings will take place in Birmingham. We can help with transport such as buses, trains or a taxi to the train station if needed.</font></li><li><font face="arial">The Regional Youth Board will review the funding pitches of local youth boards and decide on whether they are successful or not</font></li><li><font face="arial">Get to make key decisions to shape NCS graduate activity locally</font></li></ul><div><font face="arial">The first meeting will be in Birmingham city centre on Tuesday 16th February 2-4pm. Exact location to be confirmed (probably in the Bullring)</font></div></div><div><font face="arial"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial">If you can't attend, don't worry! We will send you a meeting summary afterwards.</font></div><div><font face="arial"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial">Please reply and let me know:</font></div><div><ul><li><font face="arial">If you want to be a part of <i>Regional</i> youth board</font></li><li><font face="arial">If you can attend the first meeting</font></li><li><font face="arial">If you need any help with transport and what help this might be (i.e. pay for train or a taxi to the train station)</font></li></ul><div><font face="arial">Thanks,</font></div></div><div><font face="arial"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial">Liam</font></div>]]></td>
